history.text: Have you seen Frozen?
I have! I love that movie!
So did I! I didn't realize it was based off of "The Snow Queen."
I really liked the snowman.
Olaf!! Yes, me too. I am not surprised that Rotten Tomatoes rated it 89%,
But yah, I like how it was based on teh Snow queen, I thought that was pretty cool.
Quite the story when you think about it! Who would think about giving a sister icy powers?
Eternal winter would be awful!!
The movie was really emotional!
It really was. Yet it was great for the whole family. I love Disney movies.
Me too, they're so great. I loved how fearless Ana was!
So did I! Have you heard if this has made it to Broadway yet?
I'm not sure if it's on Broadway, but it wouldn't surprise me if it were
It would make a great musical! I heard that some have said this is as deep as a Pixar film.
it really is! I was surprised Disney could pull it off as well as they did.
The voice actors they chose were perfect, I was kind of shocked at that too!
It was different from most Disney films. And I agree, the voices were great. Terrific family entertainment. Disney stepped it up a notch with this one.
I can't believe it's only the 53rd Disney film though. II would have thought they had more
The way Disney re-imagined Elsa was perfect.
Yes, that surprised me. I always loved The Little Mermaid but enjoyed this more.
Yeh, I liked the Little Mermaid, but yeah this was better. Elsa throwing away her crown was just such a moment for me. It was so freeing!
Oh definitely! Can you imagine being crowned queen when you turn 21?!
That would be frightening
I can only imagine how Elsa felt, and with ice powers too? No wonder she thought her people would fear her!
That was very freeing when she threw away her crown. But it was sad when she fled the kingdom.
It was especially sad when Elsa froze Anna's heart.
The ending was so tragic! I was so upset when he locked Ana in a room to die, how horrible!
That part when her heart got frozen was so sad for me. I elt so bad for her!
I know! I liked when Kristoff took anna to Hans to giver her her true love's kiss.
But then the shock came!!
Do you mean the trolls? Because I thought they were funny!
I was was scared when Marshmallow chased them out though, he was pretty big!
Oh yes, I loved the trolls. But didn't Kristoff race Anna home to Hans?
Yes he did, so Ana could kiss Hans. But then he tricked her.
And then Hans just locked her in that room to die...
